From Brian Ceccarelli Subject Re Is it good that Jesus died In article Ken Arromdee writes You said everyone in the That means everyone in the world including children that are not old enough to speak let alone tell If Jesus says everyone you cannot support that by referring to a group of people somewhat smaller than everyone That's Even infants who cannot speak as Even a little child will rebelliously stick his finger in a light Even a little child will not want his diaper Even a little child will fight nap So far as Jesus saying everyone A certain ruler asked Jesus Good teacher what must I do to inherit eternal life Why do you call me good Jesus No one is good except God Ken the book of Romans states that we are born We do not grow into being a We sin because we are The common mistake even in Christian circles is to think the reverse So for as surely as you grew to look like you parents you not only inherited their appearance but also their sin It goes with being Even though a new born is innocent as can be his sinful nature will surely manifest itself more explicity as he gets For as surely as he grows hair on his head and teeth within his mouth he will show the signs of his innate sin by rebelling against mommy and daddy with that loud proclamation